Description:
ANOTHER SOLD BY TIM ~ 0449 998 787
ANOTHER SOLD BY TIM ~ 0449 998 787 Desirably located in the heart of Collingwood with everything on your door step, this stunning apartment is bound to create a buzz. Bordering East Melbourne, surrounded by cafes and restaurants and just metres from Collingwood's famous entertainment precinct, Smith Street's shops, amenities and city bound trams.
This spacious top floor apartment has a flexible floorplan providing an additional open plan second bedroom layout which provides the perfect base to enjoy an inner urban lifestyle to the fullest, where you can walk or ride to virtually everything you need. Step out and enjoy Collingwood's bustling entertainment precinct and then retreat home to relax in the spacious living areas, which spills out to a private balcony with built in breakfast bar. Further offering a beautifully appointed kitchen with stone benches, dishwasher, stainless steel gas cooking and ample storage, timber flooring, as well as one secure parking space and storage cage.
Not to be missed, be quick to inspect!
Insights: 506/107 Cambridge Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2019 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Smell the coffee...Devour the lifestyle
Located in a boutique development, and just one of seventeen apartments in the bespoke "Little Ox" Building, this two bedroom apartment offers light filled living in a Fitzroy fringed pocket of Collingwood. North facing and located on level 2 at the rear of the block, the apartment is in terrific condition and has sound environmental credentials (7 star energy rating), blending seamless design with a modern fixtures and fittings. Comprises 2 well sized bedrooms with BIR's, north facing open plan living, central bathroom, delightful north facing terrace and quality appliances throughout. With security entry, lift access, storage area and more. Located moments from Smith, Gertrude & Brunswick St with public transport close by, easy Eastern Freeway access, as well as great access to MCG and CBD.

Description:
Under Offer
Contemporary designed 2 bedrooms apartment nestled in the heart of Collingwood, with everything at your doorstep! Offering you a brilliant lifestyle, positioned within the bustling Smith Street shopping district, walking distance to Gertrude and Brunswick Street cafes, restaurants, bars, and public transport, East Melbourne parks/gardens, MCG and CBD!
This lovely 2 bedrooms, 2-bathrooms and 1 car space apartment with a total size of approximately 83.8sqm on level 3 with a wonderful view facing west. This spacious apartment comprises of security entrance, stunning kitchen with stainless steel appliances and island bench adjoin open plan living space opening to the balcony, bedroom with built-in robes and a well-designed bathroom.
Further features include heating/cooling, three communal garden areas, two rooftop entertaining terraces, a library lounge, and ground-floor retail shopping. Along with both Brunswick & Smith Street shopping precincts at your fingertips.

Description:
Sensational Single Bedroom with Sweeping Views
Designed by award winning architects Elenberg Fraser, the Oxley Apartment Complex is perfectly positioned in the heart of Collingwood's Foy Heritage precinct. This stunning single bedroom is both modern & unique, offering a streamlined contemporary layout maximising natural light throughout.
The open-plan living & dining area featuring floor to ceiling windows opens unto an ultra-spacious balcony with outstretched sweeping views. The modern kitchen with stone benches, glass splashback & stainless-steel appliances. Comprising a generous and well-lit bedroom featuring mirrored built in wardrobe & ample natural light, immaculately presented bathroom with floor to ceiling tiles and high-end fittings. Other features include European laundry, double-glazed windows, block out roller blinds & split-system with heating and cooling unit.
The uniquely designed complex features lush exterior landscapes, Secure intercom entry, private lift access, and a lavish rooftop garden terrace & entertaining area featuring an outdoor BBQ & private plunge-pool. These secure yet serene building facilities provide residents with a blissful sanctuary to call home.
Located within close proximity to Smith Street bars & cafes, renowned restaurants, cosmopolitan shopping precincts, The East-Melbourne hospital precinct, Collingwood train station & trams, Fitzroy Gardens & the CBD. This apartment is a perfect opportunity for astute investors or first home buyers.

Description:
Oxley Designer Edge with a Taste of Luxury
A rare opportunity to live the life you love, this particularly sophisticated and state-of-the-art, two bedroom apartment is a part of the highly sought-after Elenberg Fraser designed Oxley building, in the thriving heart of Melbournes inner north. Surrounded by countless cafes, bars, clubs and restaurants, as well as plenty of public transport, this is a terrific chance for lifestyle-motivated owner-occupiers, professionals and savvy investors to acquire a fully secure designer domain on the city-fringe.
Perfectly designed for al fresco living and entertaining, the homes open-plan kitchen / meals / living is a great place to gather, with a central stone-topped island bench and stainless steel appliances. The space more than doubles in size as sliding glass doors open to create a seamless connection to a paved entertainers courtyard that is partly undercover and well suited to parties.
Blessed with access to a communal swimming pool and wonderful gardens, this luxurious apartment is accessed via secure video entry and offers robes in each bedroom, a vogue bathroom, European laundry and split system heating / cooling.
Just head outside and walk to the most cosmopolitan selection of Smith Sts and Fitzroys edgy café culture, vibrant nightlife, bars and eateries, whilst the city is always just moments away by tram or train and the parks of East Melbourne are easily reached for some outdoor recreation.

Description:
EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST CLOSE TUESDAY 23 JULY AT 5PM (UNLESS SOLD PRIOR)
Pivotal to all the cosmopolitan action on Smith St, yet privately tucked-away, this immaculate, 2 bedroom + study split-level apartment feels like a secluded urban oasis. Fully secure and presented in as new condition, the home allows you to enjoy the very best of inner-urban Melbourne and then retreat to your designer abode as needed.
Vast stone waterfall benches combine with Bosch appliances, under-mount sinks and mirrored splashbacks to present a sleek and sophisticated kitchen that overlooks open-plan living with a relaxed flow to the home's undercover balcony.
Meanwhile, the upstairs offers even further sense of retreat where both bedrooms share easy access to the bathroom and an open alcove study, whilst sharing a direct connection to another private balcony.
Additional features in this sophisticated designer residence include secure video entry, basement parking with a storage cage and elevator access, as well as reverse cycle heating / cooling.
Smith St is one of inner-Melbourne's most iconic and authentic strips of cafes, restaurants, bars and shops and its all just metres away, whilst the CBD and plenty of public transport are also within easy reach.
NELSON ALEXANDER PTY LTD

Description:
Sun-drenched living, Collingwood style
Sunglasses are recommended when inspecting this north facing gem... it is that light and bright!! Soak up the rays on the super generous north-facing balcony, whilst sipping on your latte from Alimentari cafe, just one of the many cafes you will be able to choose from once you call Collingwood home. With all that Collingwood and Fitzroy has to offer with an array of funky bars, pubs, live gigs and boutique shops on your doorstep. On offer is an oversized fully equipped one bedroom apartment with all the bells and whistles you need for an easy lock and leave lifestyle. Your weekends will be spent making the most of what life is all about, enjoying and living it to the fullest! Ditch the car as it's truly not needed when you literally have a tram stop at your front door or perhaps enjoy a short scenic stroll to the city instead. If you've been in search of an 'ultimate lifestyle', then this is the one you've been waiting for!

Description:
Wow-factor warehouse living - Auction on site
On the first level of the Whiteworks division of the iconic Foy & Gibson factory development, this stunning apartment represents the best of CBD-fringe living, moments from Collingwood's newest cafes, the 86 tram and the Gertrude Street design precinct. Flooded with light and retaining timber floors and other authentic industrial detail, the residence has a grand marble and mural entrance from Stanley Street. A versatile floor plan offers a spectacularly spacious living/dining room with deep original windows, open to a well-equipped kitchen (Blanco/Bosch appliances, pantry); large home office/second living room; one double bedroom (BIRs); spa bathroom/laundry and box room. With lift access to two car spaces, this exceptional property features ample storage, polished timber floors and hydronic heating.

Description:
'The Carter's Arms': an outstanding conversion, superbly positioned
This distinctive former pub (1873) in a commanding corner position, recently renovated by award-winning Workshop Architecture, is now a sensational family home suitable for work-from-home living, flooded with northerly light, with potential for conversion into two luxurious apartments. Distinguished by meticulous craftsmanship and superior inclusions, with upper-level views to Clifton Hill, the residence has been designed for energy-efficient living. Combining period appeal with clean-edged contemporary style, its versatile floor plan incorporates a family room and expansive living room flowing through French doors to an alfresco entertaining terrace with retractable awning and CBD views; custom kitchen (pantry, Bosch appliances) open to dining zone; stunning main bedroom/retreat/dressing room and two further double bedrooms; fitted home office; resort-style main bathroom (free-standing bath, walk-in shower), second bathroom and euro laundry. Including a secure garage, this remarkable property features exceptional storage, polished timber floors, zoned hydronic heating, air conditioning, double glazing and state-of-the-art security. The position speaks for itself - close to Smith and Gertrude Streets' vibrant cafes, transport, Victoria Park and the Convent Arts precinct.
Insights: 31 Gold Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2019 and 24 other 3 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Industrial revolution of warehouse space, light & style
A Manhattan mood in inner-Melbourne's most exciting warehouse precinct, this converted multi-level residence is a superbly staged design of amazing industrial-inspired space. Secured in a boutique building with basement car space, this easily-accessed 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom warehouse residence framed by high timber-beamed ceilings extends over 3 wonderfully warm, light and stylish floors. Central is a split-level living zone with sunken dining area, entertainers' kitchen and ethanol fireplace. Accommodation includes a vast air-conditioned upstairs retreat with study area, dressing room and ensuite. Downstairs a versatile lounge/office on a polished concrete floor opens to a shared cul-de-sac terrace. A stunning conversion for a sensational lifestyle near Smith and Gertrude Streets.
